You are tasked with refactoring a pair of related classes between ES6 and ES5 inheritance models. This exercise tests your understanding of prototype chains, constructor invocation, and method inheritance in both paradigms.

**Part 1: ES6 to ES5 Conversion**
Given the following ES6 class structure, rewrite `EmployeeES5` and `ManagerES5` using ES5 constructor functions and prototype-based inheritance. Ensure all methods and properties are correctly inherited.

```javascript
// ES6 Base Class
class EmployeeES6 {
  constructor(name, id) {
    this.name = name;
    this.id = id;
  }

  getDetails() {
    return `Name: ${this.name}, ID: ${this.id}`;
  }

  static companyName() {
    return 'Tech Solutions Inc.';
  }
}

// ES6 Derived Class
class ManagerES6 extends EmployeeES6 {
  constructor(name, id, department) {
    super(name, id);
    this.department = department;
  }

  getManagerDetails() {
    return `${this.getDetails()}, Department: ${this.department}`;
  }
}
```

**Part 2: ES5 to ES6 Conversion**
Given the following ES5 prototype-based structure, rewrite `VehicleES6` and `CarES6` using ES6 class syntax. Ensure all methods and properties are correctly inherited and `super` is used appropriately.

```javascript
// ES5 Base Constructor
function VehicleES5(make, model) {
  this.make = make;
  this.model = model;
}

VehicleES5.prototype.getVehicleInfo = function() {
  return `Make: ${this.make}, Model: ${this.model}`;
};

VehicleES5.totalVehicles = 0; // Static property
VehicleES5.incrementTotal = function() { // Static method
  this.totalVehicles++;
};

// ES5 Derived Constructor
function CarES5(make, model, doors) {
  VehicleES5.call(this, make, model);
  this.doors = doors;
}

CarES5.prototype = Object.create(VehicleES5.prototype);
CarES5.prototype.constructor = CarES5; // Fix constructor

CarES5.prototype.getCarInfo = function() {
  return `${this.getVehicleInfo()}, Doors: ${this.doors}`;
};
```

**Testing:**
Include small test cases for both conversions to demonstrate that instances behave as expected and `instanceof` checks work correctly for both parent and child classes.

