**Debouncing** ensures that a function (like `searchUsers` or an API call) is only executed after a specified period of inactivity (e.g., 300 milliseconds) has passed since the last time it was invoked. This is ideal for search inputs because it prevents overwhelming the system with requests for every single character typed, only performing the search when the user pauses typing.

